- App is now able to get the list of seminars properly. - Added a screen that shows the list of seminars.

- Refactored code so we have less files. - Made everything prettier using Android Studios templates. - Users now login using their nusp instead of email address. - Merged register and login button. The user will be redirected to the sign up screen if the nusp provided does not exist in the db (for now, it's not actually using the webserver). To login, use nusp: 12345 and password: 678 - The sign up screen now checks if the passwords match, if the nusp and password are long enough and if the name is not blank. - Removed email from sign up screen since the webserve doesn't have it.
- Added real login functionality?
- Fixed login and sign up not passignthe right attribute names - Separated register and login buttons
- Fixed AddSeminarActivity so it doesn't crash anymore - Made AddSeminarActivity reachable by clicking the + fab on the Seminar List screen - Added toolbars on the Add Seminar and Sign Up screens
- Fixed merge issues
- REALLY fixed merge issues
- Added search bar on the seminar list screen
- Forgot to add some new files on the previous commit. Fixed now.
- Made it so the keyboard doesn't automatically show up on the login and seminar list activities
- It's now possible to login as a teacher - Hid the add seminar button from students
- Hid 'register new teacher' button from students
- Added the new activity EditProfileActivity that'll replace RegisterUpdateActivity (no functionality yet)
- Created User class
- User class being passed from LoginActivity to editProfileActivity
- EditProfileActivity working (except for delete account button, which hasn't been implemented yet) - Moved http request to get seminar list to the SeminarListActivity since it makes much more sense

- Delete button now working on EditProfileActivity - New class HttpUtil to keep http-related code that was being repeated throughout the app - Moved HttpGetTask into HttpUtil - Removed unused variables in a bunch of files - Fixed teachers not being recognized as teachers after loging in - Fixed passwords on the profile screen not being considered passwords by the xml
- Fixed some warnings
- Added new screen to see who attended a seminar (not functionality yet) - Seminar list now clickable
